Package emissary.jni

Class JNI

  • java.lang.Object
    • emissary.jni.JNI
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class JNI
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Provide methods for retrieving native libraries from the repository The main entry point is loadLibrary. Places wishing to loadLibraries from the JniRepositoryPlace should include this class via composition and invoke this.loadLibrary rather than System.loadLibrary()
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • loadLibrary

        public void loadLibrary​(String lib)
        Load a native library, finding it if it isn't already here. First try to load the library and catch any exception. Try to ask the directory place where the JniRepositoryPlace is and see if the repository has the library we are looking for. If it comes back, save it to disk in the agreed upon location and then load it in the regular way. Throw an UnsatisfiedLinkError if this doesn't work.

        Note that System.loadLibrary expects the name as it comes back from expandLibraryName while the repository will respond to the name as it comes from filesystemLibraryName.

        Throws:
        UnsatisfiedLinkError - If it fails to load.
